The President of the Nigerian School Sports Federation (NSSF) Olabisi Joseph will be the special guest at the finals of the 16th  Doregos Inter-School Basketball championship holding today   at the school premises in Ipaja, Lagos. The tournament organized for private schools in Lagos, Ogun and Oyo states has continued to attract top schools just as the NSSF president praised the organisers for their commitment to ensuring that the tournament continues to take place annually. She however, assured that NSSF would continue to support school sports development in schools as this would engage the students as well as keep them away from social vices. She assured that the federation would help to expose the athletes to overseas sports scholarships that would aid their improvement in sports and academics.   Rohr mulls three coaching offers     Philip lauds Obaseki over equal pay for Insurance, Edo…     Club World Cup: Chelsea  stop Ighalo’s  Al- Hilal   The host team – Doregos Private Academy will be aiming for the fourth title in the boys’ event after edging out the most successful team of the competition, International School, Lagos (ISL) in the semifinal and they are expected to take on Air Force School, Ikeja in the final. - Advertisement - In the girls’ final, Topfield will slug it out against Roniks after both teams defeated Phidel College and Honeyland College in the semifinals.